    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S is a superlative example of the 996.2 generation, featuring the robust 3.6L flat-six powerplant and a Getrag six-speed manual transaxle. The mechanical provenance is documented and comprehensive; the IMS bearing has been proactively replaced with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the Bore Scoring inspection yielded a clean bill of health. The all-wheel-drive system utilizes a viscous-clutch center differential that functions flawlessly, providing optimal torque distribution. The suspension retains its factory-correct geometry, featuring refreshed control arms and Bilstein dampers that provide the precise feedback expected of a widebody 911. The braking system, characterized by four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors, shows no signs of glazing or thermal fatigue. With zero paint delamination and a pristine undercarriage free of fluid weeping, this C4S is a turn-key acquisition for the technical purist.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
